## Environment & External Services (Read-Only by Default)

You may rely on existing environment variables loaded from:

- `~/norbot-ops/products/demo/.env.local` (Supabase, app config).
- `~/pipeline/scripts/.env` (Turso, Firecrawl, Vercel, Gmail, etc.) when the user explicitly sources them.

Constraints:

- Treat these env vars as **secrets**; never print their values verbatim.
- Use them only through:
  - Existing Supabase REST patterns (`NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`).
  - Existing scripts (QA modules, tenant-builder helpers).
- When suggesting new scripts or commands, assume the user will source env files as per existing documentation.

